==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: poleaxe
<hw>poleaxe</hw></mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To fell with or as if with a poleax; -- often used
figuratively; <as>as, the entire department was <ex>poleaxed</ex> after
the takeover</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Stunned; astonished;; <as>as, we couldn't speak,
<ex>poleaxed</ex> by the sight in front of us</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polecat</ent>⟦br⟧
